gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 116, Warriors 110
gameRecap.excerpt: The Timberwolves defeated the Warriors, 116-110. Anthony Edwards recorded a team-high 33 points, along with six rebounds and seven assists for the Timberwolves, while Karl-Anthony Towns added 21 points and 14 rebounds in the victory. Stephen Curry tallied 38 points and five 3PM for the Warriors in the losing effort. Curry has notched back-to-back games with 30+ points. The Timberwolves have won their sixth consecutive game as they improve to 7-2 on the season, while the Warriors fall to 6-5.
